HEADWORD: Footpace
<hw>Foot"pace`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
walking pace or step.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dais, or elevated platform; the highest step of
the altar; a landing in a staircase.</def>
<rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

